To download and verify Zeronet via git, run the following commands in a terminal inside '''Whonix-Workstation''':

'''First install dependencies'''.

[[Qubes-Whonix]]:
If the ZeroNet qube is based on a Qubes TemplateVM, complete this action in the TemplateVM.

{{Update}}

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get update
}}

Install <code>git python-msgpack python-gevent</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install git python-msgpack python-gevent
}}

'''Install ZeroNet:'''

[[Qubes-Whonix]]:
The actual install can be done in the ZeroNet qube.

Retrieve ZeroNet's signing key. <ref>
https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/759
</ref>

{{CodeSelect|code=
gpg --recv-keys "960F FF2D 6C14 5AA6 13E8 491B 5B63 BAE6 CB96 13AE"
}}

Download ZeroNet.

{{CodeSelect|code=
git clone https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet.git
}}

Change into the ZeroNet folder.

{{CodeSelect|code=
cd ZeroNet
}}

Check the ZeroNet signature.

{{CodeSelect|code=
git log --show-signature
}}
----
'''Start ZeroNet:'''

[[Qubes-Whonix]]:

{{CodeSelect|code=
./zeronet.py --tor always --fileserver_ip $(qubesdb-read /qubes-ip)
}}

[[Non-Qubes-Whonix]]:

{{CodeSelect|code=
./zeronet.py --tor always --fileserver_ip 10.152.152.11
}}

